"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-sport-sport-olympics-tom-daley-diving-final-paris-olympics-2024-b1175760.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  Sport|Olympics  The lineup for the men's 10m platformdivingcompetition at the 2024Olympicshas been confirmed.  Noah Williams and Kyle Kothari will both be competing forTeam GBafter making it through this morning's semi-final.  China are once again the nation to beat, having dominated every diving event at these Games.  Tom Daley, who won silver with Williamsin the 10m synchro, is not involved however.  Here is all you need to know in the final event of the diving at theOlympic GamesinParis.  The final is set to begin at The Aquatics Centre at 2pm BST. There are 12 divers who will compete, including Williams and Kothari.  Daley won 10m platform bronze at London and Tokyo, before calling time on his career in the aftermath of the 2020 Games. However, he decided to make himself available for selection in July as he earned a call-up to the 10m synchro team, alongside Noah Williams.  Williams was pencilled in for both the individual and team events but Daley was only available for the synchro, such was the speedy nature of his retirement U-turn.  Teams can only pick two athletes for the individual events and Kyle Kothari was picked for the individual platform alongside Williams.  TV channel:The BBC is broadcasting two live streams of the action for the duration of the Games.\\u00a0This will be on BBC One, BBC Two or a stream available by clicking the red button on Freeview or a smart TV.\\u00a0Coverage of the diving will be across these platforms.  Live stream:Fans can also catch the BBC coverage live online for free via the BBC Sport website and BBC iPlayer. The Discovery+ app is showing extensive coverage via its app, website and on Eurosport, which begins at a monthly fee of \\u00a33.99.  Live blog:You can follow all the action viaStandard Sport'srolling live blog, with expert analysis from reporters Matt Majendie and Malik Ouzia out in Paris.  MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\"}"